{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The oceans cover some 70 percent of our planet."},{"time":3000,"text":"And I think Arthur C. Clarke probably had it right"},{"time":5000,"text":"when he said that perhaps we ought to call our planet"},{"time":8000,"text":"Planet Ocean."},{"time":10000,"text":"And the oceans are hugely productive,"},{"time":12000,"text":"as you can see by the satellite image"},{"time":14000,"text":"of photosynthesis, the production of new life."},{"time":16000,"text":"In fact, the oceans produce half of the new life every day on Earth"},{"time":19000,"text":"as well as about half the oxygen that we breathe."},{"time":22000,"text":"In addition to that, it harbors a lot of the biodiversity on Earth,"},{"time":25000,"text":"and much of it we don't know about."},{"time":27000,"text":"But I'll tell you some of that today."},{"time":29000,"text":"That also doesn't even get into the whole protein extraction"},{"time":31000,"text":"that we do from the ocean."},{"time":33000,"text":"That's about 10 percent of our global needs"},{"time":35000,"text":"and 100 percent of some island nations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"If you were to descend"},{"time":40000,"text":"into the 95 percent of the biosphere that's livable,"},{"time":42000,"text":"it would quickly become pitch black,"},{"time":44000,"text":"interrupted only by pinpoints of light"},{"time":46000,"text":"from bioluminescent organisms."},{"time":48000,"text":"And if you turn the lights on,"},{"time":50000,"text":"you might periodically see spectacular organisms swim by,"},{"time":52000,"text":"because those are the denizens of the deep,"},{"time":54000,"text":"the things that live in the deep ocean."},{"time":56000,"text":"And eventually, the deep sea floor would come into view."},{"time":59000,"text":"This type of habitat covers more of the Earth's surface"},{"time":62000,"text":"than all other habitats combined."},{"time":64000,"text":"And yet, we know more about the surface of the Moon and about Mars"},{"time":66000,"text":"than we do about this habitat,"},{"time":68000,"text":"despite the fact that we have yet to extract"},{"time":70000,"text":"a gram of food, a breath of oxygen or a drop of water"},{"time":73000,"text":"from those bodies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"And so 10 years ago,"},{"time":77000,"text":"an international program began called the Census of Marine Life,"},{"time":80000,"text":"which set out to try and improve our understanding"},{"time":82000,"text":"of life in the global oceans."},{"time":84000,"text":"It involved 17 different projects around the world."},{"time":87000,"text":"As you can see, these are the footprints of the different projects."},{"time":89000,"text":"And I hope you'll appreciate the level of global coverage"},{"time":92000,"text":"that it managed to achieve."},{"time":94000,"text":"It all began when two scientists, Fred Grassle and Jesse Ausubel,"},{"time":96000,"text":"met in Woods Hole, Massachusetts"},{"time":99000,"text":"where both were guests at the famed oceanographic institute."},{"time":101000,"text":"And Fred was lamenting the state of marine biodiversity"},{"time":104000,"text":"and the fact that it was in trouble and nothing was being done about it."},{"time":107000,"text":"Well, from that discussion grew this program"},{"time":109000,"text":"that involved 2,700 scientists"},{"time":111000,"text":"from more than 80 countries around the world"},{"time":113000,"text":"who engaged in 540 ocean expeditions"},{"time":116000,"text":"at a combined cost of 650 million dollars"},{"time":119000,"text":"to study the distribution, diversity and abundance"},{"time":121000,"text":"of life in the global ocean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":124000,"text":"And so what did we find?"},{"time":126000,"text":"We found spectacular new species,"},{"time":128000,"text":"the most beautiful and visually stunning things everywhere we looked --"},{"time":131000,"text":"from the shoreline to the abyss,"},{"time":133000,"text":"form microbes all the way up to fish and everything in between."},{"time":136000,"text":"And the limiting step here wasn't the unknown diversity of life,"},{"time":139000,"text":"but rather the taxonomic specialists"},{"time":141000,"text":"who can identify and catalog these species"},{"time":143000,"text":"that became the limiting step."},{"time":145000,"text":"They, in fact, are an endangered species themselves."},{"time":148000,"text":"There are actually four to five new species"},{"time":150000,"text":"described everyday for the oceans."},{"time":152000,"text":"And as I say, it could be a much larger number."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155000,"text":"Now, I come from Newfoundland in Canada --"},{"time":158000,"text":"It's an island off the east coast of that continent --"},{"time":160000,"text":"where we experienced one of the worst fishing disasters"},{"time":163000,"text":"in human history."},{"time":165000,"text":"And so this photograph shows a small boy next to a codfish."},{"time":167000,"text":"It's around 1900."},{"time":169000,"text":"Now, when I was a boy of about his age,"},{"time":171000,"text":"I would go out fishing with my grandfather"},{"time":173000,"text":"and we would catch fish about half that size."},{"time":175000,"text":"And I thought that was the norm,"},{"time":177000,"text":"because I had never seen fish like this."},{"time":179000,"text":"If you were to go out there today, 20 years after this fishery collapsed,"},{"time":182000,"text":"if you could catch a fish, which would be a bit of a challenge,"},{"time":185000,"text":"it would be half that size still."},{"time":187000,"text":"So what we're experiencing is something called shifting baselines."},{"time":190000,"text":"Our expectations of what the oceans can produce"},{"time":192000,"text":"is something that we don't really appreciate"},{"time":194000,"text":"because we haven't seen it in our lifetimes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"Now most of us, and I would say me included,"},{"time":200000,"text":"think that human exploitation of the oceans"},{"time":202000,"text":"really only became very serious"},{"time":204000,"text":"in the last 50 to, perhaps, 100 years or so."},{"time":206000,"text":"The census actually tried to look back in time,"},{"time":208000,"text":"using every source of information they could get their hands on."},{"time":211000,"text":"And so anything from restaurant menus"},{"time":213000,"text":"to monastery records to ships' logs"},{"time":215000,"text":"to see what the oceans looked like."},{"time":217000,"text":"Because science data really goes back"},{"time":219000,"text":"to, at best, World War II, for the most part."},{"time":221000,"text":"And so what they found, in fact,"},{"time":223000,"text":"is that exploitation really began heavily with the Romans."},{"time":225000,"text":"And so at that time, of course, there was no refrigeration."},{"time":228000,"text":"So fishermen could only catch"},{"time":230000,"text":"what they could either eat or sell that day."},{"time":232000,"text":"But the Romans developed salting."},{"time":234000,"text":"And with salting,"},{"time":236000,"text":"it became possible to store fish and to transport it long distances."},{"time":239000,"text":"And so began industrial fishing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242000,"text":"And so these are the sorts of extrapolations that we have"},{"time":245000,"text":"of what sort of loss we've had"},{"time":247000,"text":"relative to pre-human impacts on the ocean."},{"time":250000,"text":"They range from 65 to 98 percent"},{"time":252000,"text":"for these major groups of organisms,"},{"time":254000,"text":"as shown in the dark blue bars."},{"time":256000,"text":"Now for those species the we managed to leave alone, that we protect --"},{"time":259000,"text":"for example, marine mammals in recent years and sea birds --"},{"time":261000,"text":"there is some recovery."},{"time":263000,"text":"So it's not all hopeless."},{"time":265000,"text":"But for the most part, we've gone from salting to exhausting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"Now this other line of evidence is a really interesting one."},{"time":270000,"text":"It's from trophy fish caught off the coast of Florida."},{"time":273000,"text":"And so this is a photograph from the 1950s."},{"time":276000,"text":"I want you to notice the scale on the slide,"},{"time":278000,"text":"because when you see the same picture from the 1980s,"},{"time":280000,"text":"we see the fish are much smaller"},{"time":282000,"text":"and we're also seeing a change"},{"time":284000,"text":"in terms of the composition of those fish."},{"time":286000,"text":"By 2007, the catch was actually laughable"},{"time":288000,"text":"in terms of the size for a trophy fish."},{"time":290000,"text":"But this is no laughing matter."},{"time":292000,"text":"The oceans have lost a lot of their productivity"},{"time":294000,"text":"and we're responsible for it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"So what's left? Actually quite a lot."},{"time":299000,"text":"There's a lot of exciting things, and I'm going to tell you a little bit about them."},{"time":302000,"text":"And I want to start with a bit on technology,"},{"time":304000,"text":"because, of course, this is a TED Conference"},{"time":306000,"text":"and you want to hear something on technology."},{"time":308000,"text":"So one of the tools that we use to sample the deep ocean"},{"time":310000,"text":"are remotely operated vehicles."},{"time":312000,"text":"So these are tethered vehicles we lower down to the sea floor"},{"time":315000,"text":"where they're our eyes and our hands for working on the sea bottom."},{"time":318000,"text":"So a couple of years ago, I was supposed to go on an oceanographic cruise"},{"time":321000,"text":"and I couldn't go because of a scheduling conflict."},{"time":324000,"text":"But through a satellite link I was able to sit at my study at home"},{"time":327000,"text":"with my dog curled up at my feet, a cup of tea in my hand,"},{"time":330000,"text":"and I could tell the pilot, \"I want a sample right there.\""},{"time":332000,"text":"And that's exactly what the pilot did for me."},{"time":334000,"text":"That's the sort of technology that's available today"},{"time":337000,"text":"that really wasn't available even a decade ago."},{"time":339000,"text":"So it allows us to sample these amazing habitats"},{"time":341000,"text":"that are very far from the surface"},{"time":343000,"text":"and very far from light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345000,"text":"And so one of the tools that we can use to sample the oceans"},{"time":348000,"text":"is acoustics, or sound waves."},{"time":350000,"text":"And the advantage of sound waves"},{"time":352000,"text":"is that they actually pass well through water, unlike light."},{"time":354000,"text":"And so we can send out sound waves,"},{"time":356000,"text":"they bounce off objects like fish and are reflected back."},{"time":359000,"text":"And so in this example, a census scientist took out two ships."},{"time":362000,"text":"One would send out sound waves that would bounce back."},{"time":364000,"text":"They would be received by a second ship,"},{"time":366000,"text":"and that would give us very precise estimates, in this case,"},{"time":369000,"text":"of 250 billion herring"},{"time":371000,"text":"in a period of about a minute."},{"time":373000,"text":"And that's an area about the size of Manhattan Island."},{"time":376000,"text":"And to be able to do that is a tremendous fisheries tool,"},{"time":378000,"text":"because knowing how many fish are there is really critical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381000,"text":"We can also use satellite tags"},{"time":383000,"text":"to track animals as they move through the oceans."},{"time":385000,"text":"And so for animals that come to the surface to breathe,"},{"time":387000,"text":"such as this elephant seal,"},{"time":389000,"text":"it's an opportunity to send data back to shore"},{"time":391000,"text":"and tell us where exactly it is in the ocean."},{"time":394000,"text":"And so from that we can produce these tracks."},{"time":396000,"text":"For example, the dark blue"},{"time":398000,"text":"shows you where the elephant seal moved in the north Pacific."},{"time":400000,"text":"Now I realize for those of you who are colorblind, this slide is not very helpful,"},{"time":403000,"text":"but stick with me nonetheless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":405000,"text":"For animals that don't surface,"},{"time":407000,"text":"we have something called pop-up tags,"},{"time":409000,"text":"which collect data about light and what time the sun rises and sets."},{"time":412000,"text":"And then at some period of time"},{"time":414000,"text":"it pops up to the surface and, again, relays that data back to shore."},{"time":417000,"text":"Because GPS doesn't work under water. That's why we need these tools."},{"time":420000,"text":"And so from this we're able to identify these blue highways,"},{"time":423000,"text":"these hot spots in the ocean,"},{"time":425000,"text":"that should be real priority areas"},{"time":427000,"text":"for ocean conservation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"Now one of the other things that you may think about"},{"time":431000,"text":"is that, when you go to the supermarket and you buy things, they're scanned."},{"time":434000,"text":"And so there's a barcode on that product"},{"time":436000,"text":"that tells the computer exactly what the product is."},{"time":439000,"text":"Geneticists have developed a similar tool called genetic barcoding."},{"time":442000,"text":"And what barcoding does"},{"time":444000,"text":"is use a specific gene called CO1"},{"time":446000,"text":"that's consistent within a species, but varies among species."},{"time":449000,"text":"And so what that means is we can unambiguously identify"},{"time":451000,"text":"which species are which"},{"time":453000,"text":"even if they look similar to each other,"},{"time":455000,"text":"but may be biologically quite different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457000,"text":"Now one of the nicest examples I like to cite on this"},{"time":459000,"text":"is the story of two young women, high school students in New York City,"},{"time":462000,"text":"who worked with the census."},{"time":464000,"text":"They went out and collected fish from markets and from restaurants in New York City"},{"time":467000,"text":"and they barcoded it."},{"time":469000,"text":"Well what they found was mislabeled fish."},{"time":471000,"text":"So for example,"},{"time":473000,"text":"they found something which was sold as tuna, which is very valuable,"},{"time":475000,"text":"was in fact tilapia, which is a much less valuable fish."},{"time":478000,"text":"They also found an endangered species"},{"time":480000,"text":"sold as a common one."},{"time":482000,"text":"So barcoding allows us to know what we're working with"},{"time":484000,"text":"and also what we're eating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487000,"text":"The Ocean Biogeographic Information System"},{"time":489000,"text":"is the database for all the census data."},{"time":491000,"text":"It's open access; you can all go in and download data as you wish."},{"time":494000,"text":"And it contains all the data from the census"},{"time":497000,"text":"plus other data sets that people were willing to contribute."},{"time":499000,"text":"And so what you can do with that"},{"time":501000,"text":"is to plot the distribution of species and where they occur in the oceans."},{"time":504000,"text":"What I've plotted up here is the data that we have on hand."},{"time":506000,"text":"This is where our sampling effort has concentrated."},{"time":509000,"text":"Now what you can see"},{"time":511000,"text":"is we've sampled the area in the North Atlantic,"},{"time":513000,"text":"in the North Sea in particular,"},{"time":515000,"text":"and also the east coast of North America fairly well."},{"time":517000,"text":"That's the warm colors which show a well-sampled region."},{"time":520000,"text":"The cold colors, the blue and the black,"},{"time":522000,"text":"show areas where we have almost no data."},{"time":524000,"text":"So even after a 10-year census,"},{"time":526000,"text":"there are large areas that still remain unexplored."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529000,"text":"Now there are a group of scientists living in Texas, working in the Gulf of Mexico"},{"time":532000,"text":"who decided really as a labor of love"},{"time":534000,"text":"to pull together all the knowledge they could"},{"time":536000,"text":"about biodiversity in the Gulf of Mexico."},{"time":538000,"text":"And so they put this together, a list of all the species,"},{"time":541000,"text":"where they're known to occur,"},{"time":543000,"text":"and it really seemed like a very esoteric, scientific type of exercise."},{"time":546000,"text":"But then, of course, there was the Deep Horizon oil spill."},{"time":549000,"text":"So all of a sudden, this labor of love"},{"time":551000,"text":"for no obvious economic reason"},{"time":554000,"text":"has become a critical piece of information"},{"time":556000,"text":"in terms of how that system is going to recover, how long it will take"},{"time":559000,"text":"and how the lawsuits"},{"time":561000,"text":"and the multi-billion-dollar discussions that are going to happen in the coming years"},{"time":564000,"text":"are likely to be resolved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"So what did we find?"},{"time":569000,"text":"Well, I could stand here for hours, but, of course, I'm not allowed to do that."},{"time":571000,"text":"But I will tell you some of my favorite discoveries"},{"time":573000,"text":"from the census."},{"time":575000,"text":"So one of the things we discovered is where are the hot spots of diversity?"},{"time":578000,"text":"Where do we find the most species of ocean life?"},{"time":581000,"text":"And what we find if we plot up the well-known species"},{"time":583000,"text":"is this sort of a distribution."},{"time":585000,"text":"And what we see is that for coastal tags,"},{"time":587000,"text":"for those organisms that live near the shoreline,"},{"time":589000,"text":"they're most diverse in the tropics."},{"time":591000,"text":"This is something we've actually known for a while,"},{"time":593000,"text":"so it's not a real breakthrough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595000,"text":"What is really exciting though"},{"time":597000,"text":"is that the oceanic tags, or the ones that live far from the coast,"},{"time":599000,"text":"are actually more diverse at intermediate latitudes."},{"time":601000,"text":"This is the sort of data, again, that managers could use"},{"time":604000,"text":"if they want to prioritize areas of the ocean that we need to conserve."},{"time":607000,"text":"You can do this on a global scale, but you can also do it on a regional scale."},{"time":610000,"text":"And that's why biodiversity data can be so valuable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":613000,"text":"Now while a lot of the species we discovered in the census"},{"time":616000,"text":"are things that are small and hard to see,"},{"time":618000,"text":"that certainly wasn't always the case."},{"time":620000,"text":"For example, while it's hard to believe"},{"time":622000,"text":"that a three kilogram lobster could elude scientists,"},{"time":624000,"text":"it did until a few years ago"},{"time":626000,"text":"when South African fishermen requested an export permit"},{"time":629000,"text":"and scientists realized that this was something new to science."},{"time":632000,"text":"Similarly this Golden V kelp"},{"time":634000,"text":"collected in Alaska just below the low water mark"},{"time":636000,"text":"is probably a new species."},{"time":638000,"text":"Even though it's three meters long,"},{"time":640000,"text":"it actually, again, eluded science."},{"time":642000,"text":"Now this guy, this bigfin squid, is seven meters in length."},{"time":645000,"text":"But to be fair, it lives in the deep waters of the Mid-Atlantic Ridge,"},{"time":648000,"text":"so it was a lot harder to find."},{"time":650000,"text":"But there's still potential for discovery of big and exciting things."},{"time":653000,"text":"This particular shrimp, we've dubbed it the Jurassic shrimp,"},{"time":656000,"text":"it's thought to have gone extinct 50 years ago --"},{"time":658000,"text":"at least it was, until the census discovered"},{"time":660000,"text":"it was living and doing just fine off the coast of Australia."},{"time":663000,"text":"And it shows that the ocean, because of its vastness,"},{"time":666000,"text":"can hide secrets for a very long time."},{"time":668000,"text":"So, Steven Spielberg, eat your heart out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671000,"text":"If we look at distributions, in fact distributions change dramatically."},{"time":674000,"text":"And so one of the records that we had"},{"time":677000,"text":"was this sooty shearwater, which undergoes these spectacular migrations"},{"time":680000,"text":"all the way from New Zealand"},{"time":682000,"text":"all the way up to Alaska and back again"},{"time":684000,"text":"in search of endless summer"},{"time":686000,"text":"as they complete their life cycles."},{"time":688000,"text":"We also talked about the White Shark Cafe."},{"time":690000,"text":"This is a location in the Pacific where white shark converge."},{"time":693000,"text":"We don't know why they converge there, we simply don't know."},{"time":695000,"text":"That's a question for the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697000,"text":"One of the things that we're taught in high school"},{"time":699000,"text":"is that all animals require oxygen in order to survive."},{"time":702000,"text":"Now this little critter, it's only about half a millimeter in size,"},{"time":705000,"text":"not terribly charismatic."},{"time":707000,"text":"But it was only discovered in the early 1980s."},{"time":709000,"text":"But the really interesting thing about it"},{"time":711000,"text":"is that, a few years ago, census scientists discovered"},{"time":714000,"text":"that this guy can thrive in oxygen-poor sediments"},{"time":716000,"text":"in the deep Mediterranean Sea."},{"time":718000,"text":"So now they know that, in fact,"},{"time":720000,"text":"animals can live without oxygen, at least some of them,"},{"time":722000,"text":"and that they can adapt to even the harshest of conditions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"If you were to suck all the water out of the ocean,"},{"time":728000,"text":"this is what you'd be left behind with,"},{"time":730000,"text":"and that's the biomass of life on the sea floor."},{"time":732000,"text":"Now what we see is huge biomass towards the poles"},{"time":735000,"text":"and not much biomass in between."},{"time":738000,"text":"We found life in the extremes."},{"time":740000,"text":"And so there were new species that were found"},{"time":742000,"text":"that live inside ice"},{"time":744000,"text":"and help to support an ice-based food web."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"And we also found this spectacular yeti crab"},{"time":748000,"text":"that lives near boiling hot hydrothermal vents at Easter Island."},{"time":751000,"text":"And this particular species"},{"time":753000,"text":"really captured the public's attention."},{"time":756000,"text":"We also found the deepest vents known yet -- 5,000 meters --"},{"time":759000,"text":"the hottest vents at 407 degrees Celsius --"},{"time":762000,"text":"vents in the South Pacific and also in the Arctic"},{"time":764000,"text":"where none had been found before."},{"time":766000,"text":"So even new environments are still within the domain of the discoverable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769000,"text":"Now in terms of the unknowns, there are many."},{"time":771000,"text":"And I'm just going to summarize just a few of them"},{"time":773000,"text":"very quickly for you."},{"time":775000,"text":"First of all, we might ask, how many fishes in the sea?"},{"time":778000,"text":"We actually know the fishes better than we do any other group in the ocean"},{"time":780000,"text":"other than marine mammals."},{"time":782000,"text":"And so we can actually extrapolate based on rates of discovery"},{"time":785000,"text":"how many more species we're likely to discover."},{"time":788000,"text":"And from that, we actually calculate"},{"time":790000,"text":"that we know about 16,500 marine species"},{"time":793000,"text":"and there are probably another 1,000 to 4,000 left to go."},{"time":795000,"text":"So we've done pretty well."},{"time":797000,"text":"We've got about 75 percent of the fish,"},{"time":799000,"text":"maybe as much as 90 percent."},{"time":801000,"text":"But the fishes, as I say, are the best known."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804000,"text":"So our level of knowledge is much less for other groups of organisms."},{"time":807000,"text":"Now this figure is actually based on a brand new paper"},{"time":809000,"text":"that's going to come out in the journal PLoS Biology."},{"time":812000,"text":"And what is does is predict how many more species there are"},{"time":814000,"text":"on land and in the ocean."},{"time":816000,"text":"And what they found"},{"time":818000,"text":"is that they think that we know of about nine percent of the species in the ocean."},{"time":821000,"text":"That means 91 percent, even after the census,"},{"time":823000,"text":"still remain to be discovered."},{"time":825000,"text":"And so that turns out to be about two million species"},{"time":827000,"text":"once all is said and done."},{"time":829000,"text":"So we still have quite a lot of work to do"},{"time":831000,"text":"in terms of unknowns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833000,"text":"Now this bacterium"},{"time":835000,"text":"is part of mats that are found off the coast of Chile."},{"time":838000,"text":"And these mats actually cover an area the size of Greece."},{"time":840000,"text":"And so this particular bacterium is actually visible to the naked eye."},{"time":843000,"text":"But you can imagine the biomass that represents."},{"time":846000,"text":"But the really intriguing thing about the microbes"},{"time":848000,"text":"is just how diverse they are."},{"time":850000,"text":"A single drop of seawater"},{"time":852000,"text":"could contain 160 different types of microbes."},{"time":854000,"text":"And the oceans themselves"},{"time":856000,"text":"are thought potentially to contain as many as a billion different types."},{"time":859000,"text":"So that's really exciting. What are they all doing out there?"},{"time":862000,"text":"We actually don't know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864000,"text":"The most exciting thing, I would say, about this census"},{"time":866000,"text":"is the role of global science."},{"time":868000,"text":"And so as we see in this image of light during the night,"},{"time":870000,"text":"there are lots of areas of the Earth"},{"time":872000,"text":"where human development is much greater"},{"time":875000,"text":"and other areas where it's much less,"},{"time":877000,"text":"but between them we see large dark areas"},{"time":879000,"text":"of relatively unexplored ocean."},{"time":881000,"text":"The other point I'd like to make about this"},{"time":883000,"text":"is that this ocean's interconnected."},{"time":885000,"text":"Marine organisms do not care about international boundaries;"},{"time":887000,"text":"they move where they will."},{"time":889000,"text":"And so the importance then of global collaboration"},{"time":892000,"text":"becomes all the more important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894000,"text":"We've lost a lot of paradise."},{"time":896000,"text":"For example, these tuna that were once so abundant in the North Sea"},{"time":899000,"text":"are now effectively gone."},{"time":901000,"text":"There were trawls taken in the deep sea in the Mediterranean,"},{"time":904000,"text":"which collected more garbage than they did animals."},{"time":906000,"text":"And that's the deep sea, that's the environment that we consider to be"},{"time":909000,"text":"among the most pristine left on Earth."},{"time":911000,"text":"And there are a lot of other pressures."},{"time":913000,"text":"Ocean acidification is a really big issue that people are concerned with,"},{"time":916000,"text":"as well as ocean warming, and the effects they're going to have on coral reefs."},{"time":919000,"text":"On the scale of decades, in our lifetimes,"},{"time":922000,"text":"we're going to see a lot of damage to coral reefs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":924000,"text":"And I could spend the rest of my time, which is getting very limited,"},{"time":927000,"text":"going through this litany of concerns about the ocean,"},{"time":929000,"text":"but I want to end on a more positive note."},{"time":931000,"text":"And so the grand challenge then"},{"time":933000,"text":"is to try and make sure that we preserve what's left,"},{"time":935000,"text":"because there is still spectacular beauty."},{"time":937000,"text":"And the oceans are so productive,"},{"time":939000,"text":"there's so much going on in there that's of relevance to humans"},{"time":942000,"text":"that we really need to, even from a selfish perspective,"},{"time":945000,"text":"try to do better than we have in the past."},{"time":947000,"text":"So we need to recognize those hot spots"},{"time":949000,"text":"and do our best to protect them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":951000,"text":"When we look at pictures like this, they take our breath away,"},{"time":953000,"text":"in addition to helping to give us breath"},{"time":955000,"text":"by the oxygen that the oceans provide."},{"time":957000,"text":"Census scientists worked in the rain, they worked in the cold,"},{"time":960000,"text":"they worked under water and they worked above water"},{"time":962000,"text":"trying to illuminate the wondrous discovery,"},{"time":964000,"text":"the still vast unknown,"},{"time":966000,"text":"the spectacular adaptations that we see in ocean life."},{"time":969000,"text":"So whether you're a yak herder living in the mountains of Chile,"},{"time":972000,"text":"whether you're a stockbroker in New York City"},{"time":975000,"text":"or whether you're a TEDster living in Edinburgh,"},{"time":977000,"text":"the oceans matter."},{"time":979000,"text":"And as the oceans go so shall we."}]},{"cues":[{"time":981000,"text":"Thanks for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":983000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}